And the reading and spelling grrrrr!<br>
They ask the kid's to spell a word the way they think it is spelled and let it go at that, it's called Creative Spelling.  Look at these boards, i would guesstimate a lot of the people who post here were taught the same way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E7D7B5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub18.ezboard.com/uzoth86.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zoth86</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>MithMarr Squire</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#330000>(5/13/02 10:06:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub18.ezboard.com/fmithanielmarrdailynewsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1098.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: School systems</span><hr size=1> The problem is a group of &quot;expanded minds&quot; in the early 70's sold schools on the idea that telling a child, &quot;no, sorry, thats not correct&quot; can so damage their poor little psyche that they can never become viable, left wingnut tree hugging members of &quot;society&quot;.<br>
<br>
The bottom line, people, is that like it or not there ARE absolutes in life! There are such things as right and wrong, and teaching children otherwise ONLY breeds a generation of soft thinkers that are firmly convinced that opinions and feelings mean far more than facts and thoughts.<br>
<br>
But I cant blame the teachers...with frighteningly few exceptions most school teachers are poor embittered souls that got into teaching in the first place because they liked the idea of sitting in &quot;discussion circles&quot; to mold and shape young minds for 9 months out of a year, then getting summers off to surf....then they discovered teaching was REAL WORK (boohoo). No, I have to blame the parents. They allow schools to raise their children, blindly trusting an oh, so obviously flawed &quot;it takes a village&quot; approach to raising a child, rather than following the tried, trusted and true method of &quot;strong family, strong children&quot;.<br>
<br>
For God's sake, people, get involved in your children's education! KNOW what information is being spoon fed to your kids in schools!! The government cant even be trusted to balance its own checkbook, and you are gonna let them raise your child???<br>
<br>
Just my 2 bits (for those of you from public schools thats 25 cents).<br>
